name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
Recently, a video of a giant panda being urged to go home by a keeper with a bamboo pole has been circulated on the Internet, and netizens have questioned the keeper's behavior of hitting the giant panda with a bamboo pole.
On April 17, Nanjing Ziqing Lake Wildlife World issued an apology letter stating that the keeper involved will immediately stop working and will never be allowed to raise giant pandas in the park.
Some netizens compared this incident with the previous incident of a teacher at a middle school in Jinan, Shandong, who physically punished students, and lamented that people are not as good as pandas.

Performance Art in China:
On a newly replaced bulletin board at a university in Changchun, the masks of each NPC representative were thoughtfully photoshopped onto their faces using photo-editing software, presumably to ensure accurate memory.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On April 18, my Alipay account was frozen by the court.
In December last year, when the company I founded in China was cancelled, a stranger reported that I owed wages (in fact, we had never hired any employees).
In March, the school I worked and cooperated with in Italy received an anonymous collective report from Milan, claiming that I had defrauded their tuition fees. (In fact, I did not engage in teaching or study abroad business in Milan) But considering the impact of my existence, the school terminated all cooperation and business with me.
In March, a Chinese in Italy (news materials showed that he was the chairman of a multinational tourism group) went to the house where I lived when I was in school and wanted to "talk" with me.
In April, my NetEase BUFF and Alipay were successively frozen by the court.
So far, all my sources of income have been cut off by relevant Chinese authorities.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
In this case, I can only put aside my pride and ask for your help

Everyone is welcome to donate to help this account continue to operate.
Thank you everyone.
